			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">One "clue banana" coming up:

http://www.petalia.com.au/Templates/ProdSubList.cfm?specie=Dogs&Group;_No=6225



Hmm..maybe you can get ittoolbox to get some embroadered (sp?) with their logo to give out at the close of each story for "he who guessed the butler doneit soonest".



"Guess whodoneit...and how...and their IP address, router brand they compromised, and packet flags they set to bypass the NAT and you too could win!"



Interestingly enough, in most of these I've noticed that it's not "the hot 'sploit-o-the-day" that caused the problem.  Nor "the virus that ate the internet".



People are sneaky and will find holes even when you think you've patched them all.



Current case in point.  What could ISH have done to prevent this?  Have alerts catch it faster?  (things that they reasonably should have had in place for their industry, security tolerance, etc)



