			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">Great story! Shows just how important physical safeguards are for a data center. Access should be limited as much as possible to critical systems and equipment. A cheap CCTV setup with digital archiving at the entry points and internally would have saved them a lot of time and money. Of course then we wouldn't have heard about this interesting case and the veiled warning about unsecured corporate WLAN setups (I mean the neighboring company's).



Did they feel the sting of the clue bananna across the face on this one?</span>
