			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">Oops!  I left something out.



I just realized that I didn't explain the part of the investigation that helped us locate Mark.  



Once we identifed Mark as Jeremy's roomie, we did a drive-by on Jeremy's house and wrote down makes/models of the vehicles in the carport.   Mikel and the ITD had this information and were keeping the parking lot under surveillance with the help of their facility security company.



This is one of those cases where there was a lot of work up front, and then it came together rather quickly in the end.  



As one of my readers (the P.I.) pointed out - trust the evidence.  Most of the important information and clues are almost always right under your nose.  



And drink a good brand of coffee - like Seattle's Best.  :-)</span>
		</div>
           
